## Example 3 — Scale Drawing Problem

An architect draws a floor plan at a scale of 1 inch : 4 feet. On the plan, a room measures 3.5 inches by 5 inches. Find the actual dimensions and area of the room.

### Step 1: Convert Plan Dimensions to Actual Dimensions

$$\text{Actual length} = 3.5 \times 4 = 14 \text{ feet}$$

$$\text{Actual width} = 5 \times 4 = 20 \text{ feet}$$

### Step 2: Find the Actual Area

$$A = 14 \times 20 = 280 \text{ square feet}$$

### Step 3: Verify with the Plan Area

$$\text{Plan area} = 3.5 \times 5 = 17.5 \text{ square inches}$$

The scale factor for area is $k^2 = 4^2 = 16$:

$$17.5 \times 16 = 280 \text{ square feet} \checkmark$$

✅ Answer: The room is **14 ft × 20 ft** with an area of **280 square feet**.

